[Although the majority of Japanese encephalitis (JE) cases, often reported with cases of acute encephalitis syndrome (AES), occur in the northeastern states of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar and Assam, JE cases are also reported from other states including Punjab. The single confirmed JE case reported above indicates that the JE virus transmission season has begun. No mention is made in the report above of plans to vaccinate people residing in the locality where the case occurred. Increased surveillance is prudent. - Mod.TY

